Pre-Game Insights: Gabadinho Mhango, a key player for Moroka Swallows, has been dropped from Malawi's squad for the upcoming World Cup qualifying match against São Tomé and Príncipe on June 6, 2024.
Coach Patrick Mabedi has not provided reasons for Mhango's exclusion.
Richards Bay striker Khuda Muyaba has also been sidelined, with Brighton Munthali being the only South Africa-based player in the squad.
The foreign-based players in the squad include Henri Kumwenda, Chawanangwa Kaonga, Chifundo Mphasi, John Banda, and Chembezi Denis.
